<br>
1)4 shadowed claws dropped from random shades in the area, give to the merchant looking cat about 8 seconds run down the road from town for 5 ac 10 hp boots.<br>
<br>
2)give the merchant beside the banker outside town 4 claws from the level 1 rockhoppers and he gives you a sewing needle, haven't found what its for yet...<br>
<br>
3)give one of the firedancers 4 remains of loada'kai not sure of result...<br>
<br>
any additions would be appreciated... <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/utabbalt.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Tabb Alt</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(12/8/01 6:24:09 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3441.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Low Level Vah'Shir Quest List</span><hr size=1> An alchemist near the palace (in one of the libraries) says he is looking for someone who wants work.<br>
<br>
He asks the worker to gather a red mushroom, a blue mushroom, and a peice of scarlet moss.  All 3 are found as ground spawns under the bridges in the newbie area for the cats (Aka, the pit)<br>
giving these items to him results in some acrylia powder, which can be turned in for cash and xp to the person who makes your acrylia plate. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ubarrister.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Barrister</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.thesafehouse.org/images/ring20.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(12/9/01 9:11:06 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3441.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Low Level Vah'Shir Quest List</span><hr size=1> Tabb, you have the name for that alchemist? I found all the bits, but cant find the right person to turn them in to. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/udarannt.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Da Rannt</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/image/globalBlack.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(12/9/01 10:28:26 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3441.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Low Level Vah'Shir Quest List</span><hr size=1>      More Thicket Quests:<br>
<br>
      Kaza Raj near the guard tower gives out quests requiring 4 items.  He'll give info if you ask him what &quot;piece&quot;, I know for sure he's got quests for legs, gloves, boots and bracer.  Rewards seem to be no drop, slightly better then leather with a few small bonuses.<br>
      Spiritist ???, in tent near merchants, will give rewards for every 4 jaw pieces returned to her.  Two types of jaw pieces, shattered and ???.  The ??? pieces give decent sleeves, slightly better then leather some stat bonuses.  <br>
      Also in one of the tents on the other side you can get rewards for hopper scales (4 of any type shredder, hopper, etc.), not sure of the rewards.<br>
      I'm still tryin to get 4 of most of the items, I'll post back if I finish any more, most of the drops seem disappointingly rare but I could just be unlucky.<br>
<br>
Da Rannt da oger rogue<br>
800lbs o stealth <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uazhdarkhos.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Azhdarkhos</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(12/9/01 1:17:15 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3441.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Low Level Vah'Shir Quest List</span><hr size=1> Kaza Raj seems to have a quest for each of the visible pieces of armor.  From what I've found each piece is one ac above standard leather and +10 hp.<br>
<br>
Sleeves = 4 Loda Kai Earrings (seem pretty rare, killed a lot of Loda Brigands, Thugs and Poachers - found plenty of other pieces but only one earring dropped)<br>
<br>
Pants = 4 Saurek Fangs (from big saureks, forget which one exactly)<br>
<br>
Tunic = 4 Carapace from Ch'Thk Bloodbulks (haven't found these critters yet)<br>
<br>
Cap = 4 Loda Kai Insignia (kind of rare off various Loda Kai)<br>
<br>
Hymnist Omiyad wants 4 Loda Kai Remains (also kind of rare) in return for which he will give you an amulet with 4 AC, +1 Str, Cha and Wis.<br>
<br>
The needles are for making Shaded Hopper Armor.  Combine in a sewing kit (or Vah Shir Stitching Kit that newbie beastlords get) the Needle + a piece of Tattered Hopperhide Armor (made like patchwork armor, using a Damaged Hopper Hide) + the matching piece of Xakra Kel armor (a no rent armor dropped by lesser shades and Shak Dratha - armor made of spirit energy, basically).  The resulting armor has the same AC as the Tattered armor piece with and added +1 vs. Magic.  Not really worth the effort in my opinion, but an interesting diversion, and if you've got the stuff to make it anyway...<br>
<br>
Broker Fahaar (in one of the two short alleys between the palace courtyard and the center section of the city) asks if you want work and tells you to hand him your acrylia slate if you do.  Doing this gets you a four slot container in which to combine 4 Young Rockhopper Hides (these drop off Young Rockhoppers in the Pit.)  Returning the full bag gets you a Stretched Hopper Hide and a Leather Cord.  Fahaar tells you that if you wish to become his Apprentice Tailor, bring him three more full bags then return to him the 4 Leather Cords you will have.  Doing this gets you a Vah Shir Skinning Knife and a quest to make him a Rough Belt Strap (done by combining a MQ Hopper Hide and the Skinning Knife in a sewing kit) - return the belt strap and knife to the Broker.  Returning this gets you a Vah Shir Needle Kit (looks like a sewing kit, but is not a container) and a quest to make a Black Chitin Belt and a Bone Beaded Belt.  The Black Chitin Belt is made by combining the Needle Set + Xakra Thread + Rough Belt Strap + Scorpion Carapace(s?).  The Bone Beaded Belt recipe is Grimling Bone Finger (from grimling skellies in the Pit) + Rought Belt Strap + Silk String + Vah Shir Needle Kit.  I haven't made either of the last two items yet, so recipes are still in need of verification.  Also, I don't remember if the Broker returns the Vah Shir Skinning Knife to you after the middle step, so it may be necessary to repeat the first part to get another one (large pain in the posterior, but if you're a Tailor this is familiar territory.) <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table><br><font color=#FF0000>- </font><a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/bthesafehouse>The Safehouse</a><font color=#FF0000> - </font><a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm13>Quests of Norrath</a> <font color=#FF0000> - </font><a href="http://www.thesafehouse.org">The Safehouse website</a><font color=#FF0000> - </font> <center><a href="http://www.guildboss.com"><img
